article.headline: Colgate 66, Navy 58
article.story: ANNAPOLIS, Md., (AP) -- Kyle Chones scored 13 points to lift Colgate to a 66-58 victory over Navy on Saturday in a matchup of teams that had been tied for last place in the Patriot League. Chones shot 5-for-11 from the field and also grabbed six rebounds in compensating for the absence of his twin brother, who missed the game due to illness. Kendall Chones is a starter and the team's second leading scorer. The visiting Red Raiders (7-13, 2-5 Patriot League) were also without backup forward Alex Woodhouse, who was too ill to make the trip. Willie Morse came off the bench to contribute nine points for Colgate, which snapped a five-game losing streak. Greg Sprink scored 23 points to lead Navy (11-11, 1-6). Colgate scored the last six points of the first half and the initial seven points of the second half to take a 36-26 lead with 17:25 remaining. Sprink scored a pair of 3-pointers and Bryce Brigham also made one as Navy fought back to within one point at 42-41 with 10:40 to go. Sprink made a free throw on the next possession as Navy moved into the double bonus. However, instead of taking the ball to the basket or pounding it inside to get to the free throw line, the Midshipmen tried for 3-pointers on their next five possessions and missed them all. A nearly four-minute drought enabled Colgate to regain control. A 3-pointer by Morse sparked an 8-0 run that put the Red Raiders ahead 53-42 with just over seven minutes to go. Navy, which has now lost four straight and six of its last seven, would get no closer than eight points the rest of the way.
